<TITLE> Seven to die for murder of 4 in Badda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Thursday sentenced seven people to death for the murders of four people in Badda in the capital last year. Judge Md Anwar Hossain of the Speedy Trial Tribunal-1 convicted Atiqur Rahman Mamun, Shafikur Rahman Masud, Md Mahfuz, Wasim Sarker, Mohsin Sarker, Siramin Islam Nahid and Nur Alam Nuru of the murder of Alauddin Ala and three others. The court released Tushar Ahmed Palash, who went to become a state witness during trial. All but Shafikur Rahman Masud and Wasim Sarker are in jail. The convicts shot and killed Ala, Abdul Quader Masum, Tajul Islam and Rubel over a business dispute at different localities in BaddaAlatun Nesa School, Kumari Garments, Nani Bari crossing and near Khanka Sharifon Feb 7, 2006. Murdered Tajul Islam's brother Naim Uddin filed a case against eight people with Badda Police Station. Badda Police Station sub-inspector Rezaul Karim pressed charges against the eight suspects in the court. bdnews24.com/p
